added.title: BBSFBDAY!
added.description: Beast Boy agrees to share his birthday with Starfire after learning she's never had one on Earth.

added.title: BBCYFSHIPBDAY
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg celebrate the birthday of their friendship.

added.title: BBBDay!
added.description: It's Beast Boy's birthday! But will the other Titans remember?

added.title: Two Parter Part 1
added.description: The Titans visit the Hall of Justice to use the pool, but then decide to check out the inside.

added.title: Two Parter Part 2
added.description: The Titans must save the members of the Justice League from the clutches of the supervillain Darkseid.

added.title: The Scam
added.description: At Halloween show and tell, the class isn't buying Gumball's story about Gargaroth the Devourer until Carrie fakes a terrifying haunting. The kids convince the school to hire them as ghost exterminators and take their payment in Halloween candy. But when it turns out Gargaroth is real, suddenly Gumball is expected to be the town's savior.

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare-email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it, despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it, but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Carrie takes Gumball, Darwin and Anais to a real haunted house party on Halloween!

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Ghost
added.description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Frybo
added.description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

added.title: Cat Fingers
added.description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

added.title: Horror Club
added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park V
added.description: The fifth installment of Terror Tales finds Benson trying to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wish making machine.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park IV
added.description: The park guys try to keep Muscle Man awake with scary stories on a long drive so that they can meet his mom.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Regular Show Presents: Terror Tales of the Park III
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: The Creeps
added.description: Finn & Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner banquet from Count Creepystein.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: Regular Show Presents: Terror Tales of the Park II
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: It Came From The Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo!  Now, Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Trials Part 1
added.description: Following the network of GroundBridges left by the Allspark, Optimus and Megatron finally discover the Allspark, and its Guardian, Cheetor.

added.title: Regular Show: Terror Tales of the Park
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: Trials Part 2
added.description: Cheetor attempts to judge whether Optimus or Megatron are more worthy of the Allspark, but an unexpected visitor dashes all the bots' plans.

added.title: Fool Moon
added.description: Strange things start happening when Uncle Grandpa installs a moon roof in the RV.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Little Sword of Horrors
added.description: Prohyas grows a new Magisword from a tiny seed, but doesn't know that his Carnivorous Plant Magisword is a menace to Lyvsherian society until its too late!

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: Haunted RV
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa's Haunted House spirals out of control, the gang must save the teenagers stuck inside.

added.title: E. Nigma, Consulting Detective
added.description: When the Joker traps Batman, the Justice League decides against their better judgment to allow Riddler, who is trying to go straight, to help them track him down.

added.title: Harley Goes Ape!
added.description: When Gorilla Grodd takes control over Titano, the giant ape, the only person who seems to be able to override his control is the medical worker who nursed him as a chimp. She's now known as Harley Quinn.

added.title: Phased and Confused
added.description: When members of the Justice League are affected by the Phantom Zone ray and become phantom-like, their only hope for freedom is to somehow get a message to Booster Gold.

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System—the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: Watchtower Tours
added.description: When Booster Gold starts to secretly give tours of the Watchtower to make some extra cash, he inadvertently brings in a super villain disguised as a tourist.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Spooky Boo
added.description: After Clarence leads a few neighborhood kids through his homemade haunted house, Chelsea suggests they go to the high school kids haunted house for some real scares. When the gang makes a wrong turn they find themselves in a mysterious house on a hill full of creepy sounds, ghoulish shadows and mutant rat men!

added.title: Duck Lips
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa molds her mouth into duck lips, a young girl must face the consequences of her new found popularity.

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Jeff's New Toy
added.description: Jeff wants to keep his new, flying "Wrath Hover Ginsbot" toy in its box. Clarence is desperate to play with the toy. And poor Sumo is caught in the middle.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Halloween vs. Navidad
added.description: Cuando Santa Claus intenta apoderarse de Halloween, los Titanes necesitan a un par de espíritus para detenerlo.

added.title: Mano Zombie
added.description: Cuando Starfire le besa la mano, Robin jura que nunca volverá a lavársela.

added.title: Concurso de Disfraces
added.description: Hartos de que los Hive Five les ganen en el concurso de disfraces, los Titanes elaboran un plan para ganar.
